<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONCERT YAHOOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Reviewer Chris Willman was right on the mark in describing the disruptive 
"beer-guzzling yahoo" element in the audience at Jackson Browne's Aug. 12 
Amphitheater concert ("Browne Proves There's Plenty on His Mind," Aug. 14). 
</P>
<P>
But Willman was far too kind. Do these loud, obnoxious clods (who should be 
confined to arena shows) really believe that anyone wants to hear them jabber 
during songs and whistle and scream every time the performer takes a breath 
between songs? 
</P>
<P>
It had been more than 10 years since my wife and I had seen Browne. At one 
time, he could talk between songs and quiet piano solos could be performed 
without some jerk shrieking. 
</P>
<P>
But that was way back, when audiences were still listening. 
</P>
<P>
PERRY MIYAKE 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
