<HEADLINE>
<P>
AN UNSEEN SINGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In her July 28 review of the film "Distant Voices, Still Lives," Sheila Benson 
writes: ". . . an unseen, bass voice, which may even be Paul Robeson's, sings 
'There's a Man Going 'Round Takin' Names.' The voice happens to be that of 
Jessye Norman, and how Benson could mistake it for a man's voice, especially 
Robeson's, I would be interested to know. 
</P>
<P>
ROBERT SLOTTERBECK 
</P>
<P>
Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
