<TEXT>
<P>
In your editorial, you urge that we, the overburdened taxpayers, purchase a 
railroad business in which even private companies are losing money. We already 
know that Amtrak and the RTD are big losers, that MetroRail is over budget, and 
now we've got this. I am sure a "Light Rail Bond Initiative" is just around the 
corner. 
</P>
<P>
Rail proponents wrongfully assume that people want to go downtown and that 10 
years down the road they'll still be going downtown. 
</P>
<P>
To spur more flexible transportation, we'll have to repeal licensing laws that 
make it impossible for the little guy to have a taxi, mini-van, big bus or limo 
business, and that allow established companies to charge monopoly prices that 
hurt the consumer. 
</P>
