<P>
I am old enough to remember riding the Red Cars from San Bernardino, and 
perhaps (by a trolley connection) even from Redlands, to Los Angeles. With 
their 1920's technology, they went as fast as 60 mph, if my memory is correct, 
and certainly that ride outclassed the experience of driving between those 
cities under present conditions. Since then, we have mindlessly allowed 
automobiles to become the curse of the planet. We should seize the opportunity 
