<HEADLINE>
<P>
BIG-MONEY FIGHTERS DON'T HAVE HUNGER TO ENTERTAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On the evening of Aug. 14, nearly $3 million was paid to two big-name 
middleweight fighters who didn't fight. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Nunn isn't "second to none," he's a bum who runs and doesn't look cute 
doing it. 
</P>
<P>
Iran Barkley punched as if he was underwater, when he bothered to throw a 
punch. 
</P>
<P>
These big-money bouts have nearly ruined the sport of boxing. Luckily, there is 
a plethora of hungry boxers fighting on cable television every week to keep 
real boxing fans entertained. 
</P>
<P>
I salute the club fighters of American and hope Michael Nunn sleeps well at 
night, knowing that he'll never get clocked by a real punch no matter how long 
he's paid to dance around the ring and twitch his shoulders. 
</P>
<P>
JEROLD KRESS 
</P>
<P>
Culver City 
</P>
