<TEXT>
<P>
Jose Canseco of the Oakland A's apparently has plea-bargained his way out of a 
misdemeanor weapons violation and will plead no contest Aug. 31, in exchange 
for probation and a promise to perform community service, attorney Robert 
Shapiro of Los Angeles indicated. 
</P>
<P>
Canseco, 24, was arrested by police at the University of California at San 
Francisco on April 21 after a passer-by noticed a fully loaded, semi-automatic 
pistol on the floor of his parked Jaguar. 
</P>
<P>
Shapiro said that Canseco was unaware of the state's gun possession laws and 
will perform services such as conducting an autograph session at a hospital or 
taking underprivileged children to a game. 
</P>
