<P>
An appeals court on Friday agreed to a new trial for Christer Pettersson, who 
was convicted in the slaying of Prime Minister Olof Palme, the national TT news 
agency said. 
</P>
<P>
Pettersson, a 42, was sentenced to life in prison last month after his 
conviction. He denied shooting Palme and appealed. 
</P>
<P>
The prosecution also appealed because it wanted to convict Pettersson of 
attempted murder in the wounding of Palme's widow, Lisbeth. 
</P>
