<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHINA STUDENT LEADER TO STUDY AT HARVARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CAMBRIDGE, Mass. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wuer Kaixi, one of the leaders of the student pro-democracy movement in China, 
will be a visiting undergraduate student at Harvard College during the 1989-90 
school year, according to Harvard officials. 
</P>
<P>
Wuer was chairman of the Beijing Universities Students Autonomous United Assn., 
the unofficial union that coordinated the majority of student demonstrations in 
Tian An Men Square. 
</P>
