<P>
4 BISHOPS REVIVE CUSTOM OF PRESIDENTIAL MEETINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four United Methodist Bishops met recently with President Bush, reviving a 
custom that began two centuries ago but which has been absent during recent 
Administrations. 
</P>
<P>
Bishop Jack M. Tuell of Los Angeles, president of the denomination's council of 
bishops, said the audience was sought to commemorate the 1789 visit to George 
Washington by early Methodist Bishops Francis Asbury and Thomas Coke. 
</P>
