</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
GUARD LINKED TO SEX WITH FEMALE INMATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A guard at the Metropolitan Correctional Center was charged Friday with having 
sex with a female inmate, prosecutors said. 
</P>
<P>
Carmond E. McNeil, 31, of San Ysidro was charged in a one-count indictment with 
engaging in sexual activity with a woman who was serving a 2-year sentence 
stemming from a drug conviction. 
</P>
<P>
McNeil, who has been a senior correctional officer at MCC for about two years, 
is expected to be arraigned next week, Assistant U. S. Atty. Gregory A. Vega 
said. 
</P>
<P>
If convicted, McNeil could be sentence to a maximum of one year in prison and 
up to $100,000 in fines. 
</P>
<P>
Investigators were led to McNeil after another guard on rounds observed 
something "unusual," Vega said. 
</P>
