<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mortgage Rates Rise: Fixed-rate home mortgages are averaging 10.09%, according 
to a national survey released by the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp. That rate 
was up from a rate of 9.96% last week. On one-year adjustable rate mortgages, 
lenders were asking an average initial rate of 8.69% this week, up from 8.62% 
the week before. 
</P>
