<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
U.S. Cuts Untapped Petroleum Reserves: The Interior Department said it has 
lowered by 40% its estimate of untapped and undiscovered U.S. oil resources, 
reflecting in part the recent failures of promising drilling prospects in the 
West and offshore. In its first report on undiscovered U.S. oil and natural gas 
resources since 1981, the Interior Department estimated that the nation has 49 
billion barrels of crude oil outside known fields that could be discovered and 
put into production with existing technology. Eight years ago, it estimated 83 
billion barrels of undiscovered crude. One barrel equals 42 gallons. 
</P>
