<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
FOUNDATION OPENS $100,000 FUND DRIVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Senior Resources Foundation next week will begin a yearlong effort to raise 
$100,000 to benefit senior citizen programs in Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
James Straw, co-chairman of the foundation, and Peggy Weatherspoon, director of 
the Area Agency on Aging, will begin the effort Monday with 7,000 letters 
addressed to individuals throughout the county asking them to participate in 
the fund drive. 
</P>
<P>
Straw said the project is important because programs for senior citizens have 
not received an increase in government funding in 10 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
