<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOULTON PLAZA ACQUIRED BY HAWAIIAN FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Capital Solutions, a Palo Alto real estate investor, has sold the Moulton Plaza 
shopping center in Laguna Hills for $19 million to Alexander &amp; Baldwin 
Inc., a Hawaii farming and transportation concern. 
</P>
<P>
The 133,000-square-foot center -- on Moulton Parkway between El Toro Road and 
Lake Forest Drive -- is almost entirely leased. The major tenants include a 
Hughes Market, the Department of Motor Vehicles and Security Pacific Bank. 
</P>
<P>
Alexander &amp; Baldwin, a publicly traded Honolulu company, has interests in 
ocean transport, agriculture and real estate development and management. 
</P>
<P>
The purchase is part of a $100-million acquisition program run by San 
Francisco's AMB Investments Inc. for Alexander &amp; Baldwin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
